    "In object identification models, the base network, which consists of the initial few layers, is a popular design, as shown in Fig. 7.",
    "Similar to Faster R-CNN, the same VGG-16 network was utilized.",
    "SSD employs a pyramid structure with feature maps of various dimensions following the base network.",
    "As the spatial resolution of feature maps decreases, 3-D detail information was continually lost, while abstract semantic characteristics continue to expand.",
    "Due to this, features of varying depths may identify both tiny and big objects simultaneously, which is crucial for resolving the issue of changing object sizes (Li et al. 2020a, b)."
